SEARCH
Package ie.atu.sw

Interface Indexer

All Known Implementing Classes:
AlternateIndexBuilder, IndexBuilder, IndexSetup
public interface Indexer
The Interface Indexer is an abstract blueprint of an index. It specifies what the index should do, but not how it does it. Any class that declares this interface must implement all its methods.
Since:
Java 19.
